{
  "info": {
    "name": "FST-CFC Microservices",
    "_postman_id": "fst-cfc-collection-v1",
    "description": "Complete API test collection for all FST-CFC microservices.\n\n## How to use\n1. Import this file into Postman.\n2. Import the environment file `FST-CFC.postman_environment.json`.\n3. Select the **FST-CFC Local** environment.\n4. Run **Auth / Login** first — the token is saved automatically to `{{TOKEN}}`.\n5. All protected requests will use `{{TOKEN}}` in the Authorization header.\n\n## Architecture notes\n- All requests go via the **API Gateway** on `http://localhost:3001` unless noted.\n- **Application Service** (Go) and **Program Service** (Go) must be tested DIRECTLY because the gateway path mismatch (`/api/applications` vs `/inscriptions`).\n- Document Service has a rewrite rule so it works through the gateway.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "GATEWAY", "value": "http://localhost:3001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "AUTH_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:8001", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "INSTITUTION_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:8002", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "APPLICATION_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:3005", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "PROGRAM_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:3004", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "DOCUMENT_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:3006", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "NOTIFICATION_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:3007", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "REPORTING_DIRECT", "value": "http://localhost:3010", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "TOKEN", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
